-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-19_"><p class="sc-feopBa gVincu pf-20_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-hyBbPk YitzX pf-22_">Image by  AntonioGravante via Envato Elements</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-d3bb" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-epRwmx cpmRjY pf-23_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-djVWQC dKziBg"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-24_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-25_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-26_"><em><strong>Be aware, be early: Your mouth matters</strong></em></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-28_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-bb9f530b-bb9e-46a6-8af0-ba6d40b25bd1"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Every November, Mouth Cancer Action Month shines a vital spotlight on a growing health concern that often goes unnoticed - mouth cancer. Taking place from 1 to 30 November 2025, this national campaign urges individuals, organisations, and communities to come together in support of prevention, education, and early detection of this potentially life-threatening disease.
<br></span></p><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-31_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-b71fe281-33e8-47b2-8e3b-4675b7d5ecb2"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Led by the Oral Health Foundation, with support from the Mouth Cancer Foundation, this initiative aims to enhance public awareness and reduce stigma surrounding mouth cancer. The theme for 2025, “<em>#BeAwareBeEarlyYourMouthMatters</em>”, highlights the critical importance of vigilance, awareness, and prompt action in safeguarding oral health.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-34_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-35_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-36_"><strong>What is mouth cancer?</strong></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-38_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a60af0ba-6d40-425b-91bd-3e68a570e7f9"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Mouth cancer refers to cancers that occur in the oral cavity, including the lips, tongue, cheeks, floor of the mouth, hard and soft palate, sinuses, and throat. While it is a serious condition, it is often overlooked and under-discussed compared to other cancers.</span></p><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-41_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-624adf0d-6b98-40b9-8bfa-70d1dd05ea64"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The leading causes include:</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eONOlN dawdJE pf-44_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-45_">Tobacco use (smoking and smokeless)
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-47_">Alcohol consumption
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-49_">Human Papillomavirus (HPV) infection</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-51_">Poor oral hygiene
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-53_">Unhealthy diet.
</li></ul><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-55_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-452d08c2-ed72-4069-8a47-5da0b09e5f7d"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">In the UK, more than 8,000 new cases of mouth cancer are diagnosed each year, and this number is rising. Alarmingly, many of these cases are detected at a late stage, making treatment more complex and reducing survival rates.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-58_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-59_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-60_"><strong>The importance of this year’s theme</strong></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-62_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-0ef68d97-060b-40fd-9896-a0fae31df748"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The 2025 theme, “<em>#BeAwareBeEarlyYourMouthMatters</em>”, is a timely and powerful message encouraging everyone to take their oral health seriously.
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eONOlN dawdJE pf-65_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-66_">Be aware of symptoms such as persistent mouth ulcers, unexplained lumps, or red or white patches in the mouth.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-68_">Be early in seeking help - prompt diagnosis significantly increases survival rates.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-70_">Recognise that ‘’<em>Your Mouth Matters</em>’’ just as much as the rest of your body.
</li></ul><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-72_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-cde371ba-548c-4e61-a59f-f1f479d856e9"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">By reinforcing the message that early detection saves lives, the campaign aims to break the silence surrounding mouth cancer and foster a culture of proactive health monitoring.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-75_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-76_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-77_"><strong>Recognising the signs and symptoms
</strong></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-79_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-f088fc89-2a9c-446e-8c12-7e18365cf47c"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">One of the core goals of Mouth Cancer Action Month is to educate people about what to look out for. Early signs include:
</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eONOlN dawdJE pf-82_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-83_">Ulcers that do not heal within three weeks
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-85_">Persistent lumps or swellings in the mouth or neck</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-87_">Loose teeth or difficulty moving the jaw
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-89_">Unexplained bleeding, numbness, or pain</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-91_">Voice changes or sore throat.
</li></ul><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-93_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-69c1600c-3086-4db9-912f-801e73a2d064"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">If you experience any of these symptoms, consult your dentist or GP promptly. Regular dental check-ups also play a vital role in early detection.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-96_"><strong>Blue Wednesday - A day of unity and visibility
</strong></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-98_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-801e73a2-d064-47ac-8f53-7b3606f54920"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">A highlight of the month is ‘’<em>Blue Wednesday</em>’’, observed on 13 November 2025. It’s a day when individuals and organisations are encouraged to wear blue or sport blue accessories to raise awareness and show support.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-101_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-d2e86d02-a929-4b68-9652-0072eeeba948"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">‘’<em>Blue Wednesday</em>’’ provides an opportunity for workplaces, schools, and communities to engage in conversations about mouth cancer, promote early detection, and share resources that could help save lives.
<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-104_"><strong>How to get involved</strong></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-106_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-03eae6fe-7213-422b-8f68-f33512feddd8"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">There are several meaningful ways to support Mouth Cancer Action Month 2025:
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-109_"><strong>Raise awareness</strong></h3><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-111_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-14cba6c8-76a8-42d7-bb9c-41ceee49bcef"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Use your voice and platform to spread the message. Share facts and resources using the hashtag ‘’<em>#BeAwareBeEarlyYourMouthMatters</em>’’.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-114_"><strong>Book a check-up</strong></h3><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-116_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-31d46111-ba61-422d-828d-260f66985b8e"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Encourage yourself and others to schedule a dental appointment. Regular check-ups are key to identifying early symptoms.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-119_"><strong>Educate and Inform
</strong></h3><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-121_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-3f72d6ab-4182-437a-b288-33561a00ee50"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Print posters, distribute leaflets, or host awareness talks in your organisation or community.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-124_"><strong>Join ‘’<em>Blue Wednesday</em>’’</strong></h3><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-126_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-15887943-7a22-4274-9e60-8d3e32d21863"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Participate in ‘’<em>Blue Wednesday</em>’’ on 13 November by wearing blue and encouraging discussions around oral health.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-129_"><strong>Fundraise and support charities
</strong></h3><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-131_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-35b050ef-d36a-46a2-83ba-6f71d36726b1"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Host local events or participate in sponsored challenges to support the Oral Health Foundation and the Mouth Cancer Foundation.
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-134_"><strong>Why this campaign matters</strong></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-136_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-51ed9ea9-7857-4ce6-a5b8-6d837c647d6b"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">With public awareness still low, many people do not associate symptoms with something as serious as cancer. By participating in Mouth Cancer Action Month 2025, we can change that narrative. Early diagnosis leads to a 90% survival rate, compared to 50% when detected late. This campaign not only empowers individuals with knowledge but also encourages organisations to prioritise oral health in the workplace and broader community.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-139_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-140_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-141_"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-143_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-ea844156-c79b-421e-845a-013c9e40cc72"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Mouth Cancer Action Month 2025 reminds us that oral health is not something to be taken for granted. By raising awareness, learning the signs, and acting early, we can reduce the number of lives lost each year to this preventable and treatable disease.</span></p><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-146_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-af3f00af-773d-43c4-a039-0cf5fd43365f"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Let’s work together to make a difference. Because your voice, your mouth, and your life truly matter.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-149_"><strong>Supporting health awareness through training and compliance
</strong></h3><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-151_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-9b121ec4-5a01-4c9e-80cc-72ebf06830ed"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">At <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">The Mandatory Training Group</span></em></a>, we proudly support health campaigns that drive education, prevention, and early intervention. As leaders in compliance, governance, and workforce training, we recognise the importance of promoting health awareness across all sectors.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-154_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-af957cc3-46a7-4c44-9113-91ff10d5304b"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">Through our innovative platform, like <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/complyplus-regulatory-compliance-management-software" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">ComplyPlus™</span></em></a>, we help organisations embed best practices in health and safety, including the implementation of health promotion strategies in the workplace.<br>
</span></p><p class="sc-hGMjVM kxdODp pf-157_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-14c2ea40-da59-4a30-bfaf-7b524e0b7464"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">We encourage all employers to incorporate mouth cancer awareness into their wellbeing programmes and support employees in accessing regular health screenings.
<br>
